node.text:
For those of you just discovering the power of houseplants, remember one thing.
If you treat them right, they will grow! Some will grow more and larger than others, like the classic Monstera deliciosa.
So keep this in mind when selecting plants for a particular area.
You can always cut them back to keep them in line, but when they are properly cared for they cannot help getting big!!

node.text:
Single philodendron vines look good for a little while, but then over time, they look kind of sad.
As much as it pains me to cut this beautiful philodendron verrucosum x melanochrysum
I know deep down that it’s the right thing to do.
I am aiming for a nice full plant by the end of the summer!
Wish me luck🤣🤦‍♀️

What do you do with a load of small Alocasia, well one thing you can do is combine them all into one pot.

Anyway, I hope you have a  wonderful weekend - with or without a pot filled with Alocasia 🤣

node.text: As you may have figured out, I am a serious vine lover!  Pothos, Philodendron, Hoya, Syngonium, Monstera…I love them all for their lushness and fast-growing vines! Check stories for an incredible deal on all Vining plants today on our website!💚 #get_planted #philodendron #viningplants #hangingplants

node.text: This is my favorite place to work…Chubbs and Carson are in sleep mode most of the day so I get to have company AND quiet! I’ve given prime placement to this large terra cotta planter filled with 6 different #sansevieria varieties, one of my favorite plants for styling. To see how I put this combination pot they get, check out the most recent video on the Planterina channel. 💚#get_planted #snakeplants #chillvibes #porchdecor #pottedplants
